The paper focuses on the effect of attention in deep neural networks, specifically proposing a new attention module that can be integrated with any feed-forward convolutional neural network. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves training the module in an end-to-end manner, which suggests it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of attention in natural language processing (NLP) has also been a popular research topic, so the paper may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments on image classification and object detection benchmarks, which suggests it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
